<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="1223" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[160,1155,360,558]" box="[160,248,360,385]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,248,360,385]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223">Biology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[160,1155,360,558]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223">
All specimens of this intriguing new species were collected by S. Maehara. According to him, 
<specimenCount box="[217,344,430,454]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
adult (collected in 2005) was crawling on a fallen Japanese elm, 
<taxonomicName authority="Planch" authorityName="Planch" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ulmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davidiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223">Ulmus davidiana</emphasis>
Planch
</taxonomicName>
; two additional females (in 2006) were collected by beating a fungal rotten log. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasunaga and Yamada" authorityYear="2017" box="[289,443,499,523]" class="Insecta" family="Microphysidae" genus="Loricula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nikko">
<emphasis box="[289,443,499,523]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223">Loricula nikko</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasunaga &amp; Yamada" authorityYear="2017" box="[656,800,499,523]" class="Insecta" family="Microphysidae" genus="Loricula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miyamotoi">
<emphasis box="[656,800,499,523]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1223">L. miyamotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the population density of the former is even lower. No other information is currently available.
</paragraph>
